The analysis of the variance of the number of key comparisons could suggest that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the expected number of key comparisons and exchanges, which could indicate that it belongs to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
